{
  "name": "11262-secrets-regex-startup-empty",
  "target_process": "warp-oss",
  "_purpose": "Reproduction evidence for warpdotdev/warp#11262. Runs against a warp-oss binary built WITHOUT the DEMO-PATCH-B subscription in secret_regex_updater.rs \u2014 i.e. the runtime SECRETS_REGEX is compiled ONLY when CustomSecretRegexListChanged fires, never on a SafeModeSettings toggle change, so the regex set stays empty across the whole session. The recipe proves: even after the user flips the toggle ON in the UI and the 'Secret visual redaction mode' dropdown appears (visual proof safe_mode_enabled=true at runtime), saving an MCP server config that embeds the deterministic placeholder `sk-FAKE0000000000FAKEdemoWARP11262` is NOT blocked. The save succeeds and the server lands in MY MCPS \u2014 because find_secrets_in_text consulted the still-empty SECRETS_REGEX and returned [], so PR #10839's predicate gated on contains_secrets=false.",
  "_safety": "Token is the deterministic placeholder `sk-FAKE0000000000FAKEdemoWARP11262`. Matches the Generic SK regex from custom_secret_regex_list \u2014 the very regex that SHOULD have detected it.",
  "_state_touched": "Adds MCP entry `demo-regex-empty-11262` to MY MCPS. Toggles Secret redaction OFF \u2192 ON (ends ON so a follow-up recording can be done without re-priming).",
  "_phases": [
    "A: open Settings, search 'redaction'; visually confirm toggle starts OFF",
    "B: click toggle ON; wait for 'Secret visual redaction mode' dropdown (proves UI says safe_mode_enabled=true)",
    "C: navigate to MCP Servers \u2192 + Add \u2192 paste config with sk- in headers.Authorization",
    "D: click Save \u2192 expect demo-regex-empty-11262 to appear in MY MCPS (BUG: should have been blocked; SECRETS_REGEX is empty because no subscription compiled it)"
  ],
